Privacy Policy for the PHANTOMs Discord Bot

Last updated: 29/08/2025

1. Information We Collect

The Bot may collect and temporarily store the following information:

Discord data: Server IDs, channel IDs, and user IDs for command usage and logging configuration.

Roblox data: Roblox usernames, user IDs, and role/rank information retrieved via the Roblox API.

The Bot does not collect or store personal information beyond what is necessary to provide its features.

2. How Information is Used

To log join, leave, and rank-change events in the designated Discord channel.

To execute the /rankup command and update Roblox ranks.

To remember configuration choices (e.g., which channel is set for logging).

3. Data Storage

Server configuration and member snapshots are stored locally on the botâ€™s host.

No data is sold, shared, or used for advertising.

Data may be cleared or reset at any time by the Bot owner.

4. Third-Party Services

The Bot uses APIs from:

Discord (to run slash commands and send messages).

Roblox (noblox.js) to retrieve and update group member information.

Both services have their own terms and privacy policies.

5. Security

Your Roblox .ROBLOSECURITY cookie is stored privately in environment variables and never shared.

Access to stored data is restricted to the Bot owner.

6. Your Rights

You may remove the Bot from your server at any time, which stops all data collection and processing.

You may request deletion of stored server data by contacting the Bot owner.

7. Contact

If you have any questions, concerns, or requests regarding these Terms or this Privacy Policy, please contact the Bot owner directly via Discord.
